     <div type="encomium">
   <head>In Amicum Willielmum Barriff.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <seg rend="decorInit">Y</seg>Oung, and so old in <hi>Martiall Discipline?</hi>
      </l>
      <l>Distrust will say, This work is none of thine.</l>
      <l>But I, that know it, will averre the same</l>
      <l>To be thine owne, and not anothers fame.</l>
      <l>A noble <hi>Souldier</hi> scorns to be so base</l>
      <l>By others Worth to purchase his owne Grace.</l>
      <l>Aud such is <hi>BARRIFF.</hi> What his Booke doth speake,</l>
      <l>It is his owne: Let Envie swell and breake.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>Amicus H. P.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
